    "a-abstract": {
      "type": "elementBody",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Legibility is not a fixed property of a typeface. It is produced in the relationship between a typeface, a body size, a line-height, a contrast ratio, an ambient light level, and a reader's familiarity with the form. This paper attempts to disentangle these variables and offer working guidelines for text design across digital environments.",
